Project GURUHA

GURUHA is an acronimous from GURPS RUles HAcks. It's a java programming API to 
abstract the GURPS rules, intented to be used in programs capables to aid any
kind of GM or player to build up adventures, characters, roll dices, simulate 
GURPS combat, play on-line, etc.

The current version is on alpha release and have a few features yet.

- To build the jar, run ant dist
- To run the test suit, run ant tests
- To build the javadoc, run ant docs
- To build, make the tests, build the jar and create javadoc, run ant all.
